<subSubSection id="748C08FAFF8C500637A89328067F91C1" pageId="2" pageNumber="67" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="3C295B71FF8C500637A8932802CE91ED" blockId="2.[151,1437,1869,2040]" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">
<emphasis id="0EE28763FF8C500637A8932802479151" bold="true" box="[151,274,1869,1896]" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Lateral oral margins not produced. Scutum entirely short yellow pilose. Scutellum roughly semicircular, with very small calcars. Propleuron with microtrichia. Abdomen narrow, less than 1.5 times the width of the thorax. Lateral margins of the abdomen are markedly thickened except at the junction of terga II and III. Length ratio of terga III–IV about 1: 1.
</paragraph>
